liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The president of Indonesia, home to the world's biggest Muslim population, has called for a ceasefire ahead of meeting US President Joe Biden in Washington. "A ceasefire must be implemented soon, we also must accelerate and increase the amount of humanitarian aid, and we must begin peace negotiations," President Joko Widodo said in a video recorded after he took part in an Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) in Riyadh. He said the world seemed "helpless" in the face of the suffering of the Palestinians. The extraordinary joint Islamic-Arab summit also urged the International Criminal Court to investigate "war crimes and crimes against humanity that Israel is committing" in the Palestinian territories.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Indonesia president calls for ceasefire ahead of meeting with Biden

children.content: The president of Indonesia, home to the world's biggest Muslim population, has called for a ceasefire ahead of meeting US President Joe Biden in Washington.

"A ceasefire must be implemented soon, we also must accelerate and increase the amount of humanitarian aid, and we must begin peace negotiations," President Joko Widodo said in a video recorded after he took part in an Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) in Riyadh.
He said the world seemed "helpless" in the face of the suffering of the Palestinians.

The extraordinary joint Islamic-Arab summit also urged the International Criminal Court to investigate "war crimes and crimes against humanity that Israel is committing" in the Palestinian territories.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Israeli President Isaac Herzog denies Israel is striking Gaza's Al Shifa facility. The largest hospital in Gaza is reportedly sheltering thousands of Palestinians and has run out of fuel. But Mr Herzog says "everything is operating" at the hospital. Speaking to the BBC, he calls the claims "a lot of a spin by Hamas". "We deny this at all, there is a lot of spin by Hamas â¦ but there's electricity in Shifa, everything is operating," Mr Herzog says. The World Health Organization (WHO) said it had lost communication on Saturday with the hospital before it was restored Sunday. WHO director-general Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus says the hospital situation is "dire and perilous" and that it had been three days without electricity and water. The United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs says water tanks, a cardiovascular facility and the maternity ward have been damaged.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Israel's prime minister has begun to outline Israel's post-war plans for Gaza. However, they could contrast sharply with the US's vision. Benjamin Netanyahu says he would like to see Gaza would be demilitarised. Israel would retain the ability to enter Gaza freely to hunt down Hamas, he says. Benjamin Netanyahu also rejected the idea the Palestinian Authority, which administers parts of the Israeli-occupied West Bank, would control Gaza. Secretary of State Antony Blinken has previously said the US opposes an Israeli reoccupation of Gaza. The US envisions a unified Palestinian government in Gaza and the West Bank as a step toward a Palestinian state, something long opposed by Mr Netanyahu's government. Reporting with AP
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: No sign of Palestinian Authority control in Netanyahu's post-war plans

like to see Gaza would be demilitarised.
Israel would retain the ability to enter Gaza freely to hunt down Hamas, he says.
Benjamin Netanyahu also rejected the idea the Palestinian Authority, which administers parts of the Israeli-occupied West Bank, would control Gaza.
Secretary of State Antony Blinken has previously said the US opposes an Israeli reoccupation of Gaza.
The US envisions a unified Palestinian government in Gaza and the West Bank as a step toward a Palestinian state, something long opposed by Mr Netanyahu's government.
